    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nvim --listen` passes its argument to [uv_pipe_bind](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/da58fe8fd27510bb68db91b7d67264737e2279a2/src/nvim/event/socket.c#L165), which passes it to [uv_pipe_bind2](https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/44125af62afa285af6fe581dfa2daa3ca85a7983/src/unix/pipe.c#L71) with `flags = 0`, which [truncates the path](https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/44125af62afa285af6fe581dfa2daa3ca85a7983/src/unix/pipe.c#L108) if it's too long. The length is platform-dependent, but it's a bit over 100 characters on macOS and Linux. As a result, when passed a too-long path, **the path accessed is truncated silently but the error message is not**, making the error message incorrect.\n\nThe workaround is obvious: use a shorter path. But in order to know that this is the workaround, you have to understand that the silent path truncation is going on.\n\nThe default value of `$TMPDIR` on macOS is 49 characters; my listen address was simply `$TMPDIR/nvim/${PWD//\\//-}` when I encountered this error.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n$ nvim --listen /var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide --embed -p\nnvim: Failed to --listen: address already in use: \"/var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide\"\nMore info with \"nvim -h\"\n\n$ ls /var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide\n\"/var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide\": No such file or directory (os error 2)\n\n$ ls -l /var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/\nsrwxr-xr-x@ - rpatterson 31 Mar 10:24 -Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovid\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf nvim called uv_bind_pipe2 directly with UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE, then the error would look something like this.\n\n```\n$ nvim --listen /var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide --embed -p\nnvim: Failed to --listen: invalid argument: \"/var/folders/g7/9y_ydbnj2fs_fvp8xf44p8gc0000gn/T//nvim/-Users-rpatterson-Projects-src-github.com-neovide-neovide\"\nMore info with \"nvim -h\"\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim doesn't support --listen\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.8.4 (23J319)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nmacports",
