            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hi @CGamesPlay and maintainers,\nI've been experiencing this same issue and I'd like to contribute a fix. I can see that the core issue is the silent path truncation when uv_pipe_bind is called without the UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE flag.\nProposed Solution:\nReplace the uv_pipe_bind() call with uv_pipe_bind2() using the UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE flag. This would:\n\nPrevent silent truncation\nProvide clear error messages when paths are too long\nHelp users understand the actual problem immediately\n\nI'd be happy to:\n\nSubmit a PR implementing this fix\nAdd appropriate error handling for path length validation\nWrite tests to ensure the fix works across different platforms\n\nI'm Parth Patel, a third-year IT student with experience in C/C++ and system programming. I'm also looking at GSoC opportunities and would love to contribute to Neovim.\nWould this approach work for the maintainers? I can start working on a patch if this solution is acceptable.",
