            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for the quick feedback!\n\nTradeoffs/risks I can see\n\n1. \"Behavior change\": Currently long paths fail silently (truncated socket created). With `UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE`, they'll fail explicitly with `UV_EINVAL`. This is the desired behavior, but any scripts/tools relying on the current truncation would break.\n\n2. \"Lib uv version requirement\": `UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE` was added in lib uv 1.46.0 (May 2023). Need to verify Neovim minimum lib uv version supports this. *Checking now...*\n\n3. \"Cross-platform behavior\": The flag is Unix-specific (Windows doesn't have this path limit for named pipes). Should be fine since the code path is already Unix-only.\n\n- Current behavior is objectively broken (error messages lie about the path)\n- UV_PIPE_NO_TRUNCATE exists specifically for this use case\n- Fail-fast is better than silent corruption\n\nI'll work on a PR with:\n- The `uv_pipe_bind2()` change\n- Clear error message for path-too-long case  \n- Test case reproducing the original issue\n- Verification it works on macOS/Linux\n\nShould have something ready in the next few days. Will update here once the PR is up.",
